12/11/2009
ATHENS, Greece -- Authorities arrested three Turkish nationals Wednesday (November 11th) -- the captain of a cargo ship, his assistant and a mechanic -- on the island of Milos in the Aegean Sea, after finding a parcel of cannabis onboard. 
The drugs were in a metal box discovered during a routine inspection of the ship. 
The exact amount of the cannabis that was seized has not been announced. 
The ship, sailing under a Turkish flag, was loaded in Libya. 
(MIA, ANA-MPA - 11/11/09)
